column1: #Text=Wikinews Interviews Australian wheelchair basketball player Caitlin de Wit
#Text=Thai-Japanese Bangkok Youth Center , Bangkok — Wikinews interviewed Caitlin de Wit , of the Australia women 's national wheelchair basketball team , known as the Gliders .
#Text=The Gliders are in Bangkok , Thailand , for the Asia – Oceania Zone Wheelchair Basketball Championships , which are being held at the Thai-Japanese Bangkok Youth Center .
#Text=Wikinews caught up with her on Tuesday , before the Gliders ' match against China .
#Text=Georgia Inglis at the Thai-Japanese Bangkok Youth Center , Bangkok , during the Asia-Oceania Zone Championships
#Text=And I grew up on the Central Coast .
#Text=A I believe you had a horse riding accident ?
#Text=I had a horse riding accident in Wagga .
#Text=What sort of horse riding were you doing ?
#Text=We were just like out on a ride .
#Text=And you were at uni[versity ] at the time ?
#Text=Yeah , I was at uni in Wagga and that 's where I had my accident .
#Text=And I went obviously to hospital for a little while and rehab and then I moved back to Wagga to finish my degree .
#Text=I ran a little bit , and I rode horses .
#Text=And then in my first year of uni I started soccer .
#Text=That was my first team sport that I played .
#Text=So what made you take up basketball ?
#Text=I suppose when I lefty hospital I was a bit bored .
#Text=I just joined the local Wagga team .
#Text=I do n't know if its still there .
#Text=And then I joined ... and then Sarah Stewart saw me at a juniors ' camp .
#Text=And I joined what was then the Hills Hornets in the women 's league .
#Text=So you played with the Hills Hornets .
#Text=Did they win the championships that year ?
#Text=They won for a series of years straight ...
#Text=We had one win as the Flames .
#Text=And you joined the junior Australian women 's team ?
#Text=And where did you go with them ?
#Text=We went to Canada for the under 25 World Championships .
#Text=And you 're still playing with the Flames in Sydney .
#Text=And you played for the Gliders at the Osaka Cup ?
#Text=And that was in January this year ?
#Text=And that was your first trip overseas with the senior side
#Text=And now this is therefore your second trip with the Gliders ?
#Text=My family traveled a little bit as a kid , so ...
#Text=Have you played anywhere overseas with any other teams ?
#Text=So how are you enjoying it here in Bangkok ?
#Text=I keep worrying about whether they are going to blockade the airport when we need to get out of here .
